{%- comment -%}
  This snippet renders a button with customizable label, URL, and style.

  Parameters:
  - button_label: the text to display on the button
  - button_url: the URL the button links to
  - button_type: the style of the button (e.g., 'primary', 'outline')
  - section_class: a CSS class prefix for styling the button

  Required parameters:
  - button_label
  - button_url
  - section_class

  Usage:

  {%- render 'button',
      button_label: 'Click me',
      button_url: '/your-link',
      button_type: 'primary',
      section_class: 'your-class'
  -%}
{%- endcomment -%}

<span class="{{- section_class -}}__btn-wrapper">
  <a href="{{ button_url }}" class="{{- section_class -}}__btn btn{% if button_type == 'primary' %} btn--primary{% elsif button_type == 'outline' %} btn--outlined{% endif %}">
    {{- button_label -}}
  </a>
</span>
